<Author>MWSydney
<Content>Good 3 star for Centro I stayed at Hotel Roble for about 10 days in Dec 07. Overall it麓s a very decent hotel if you want a budget place to stay in Centro. Rates were 275 pesos per night. Staff were friendly  helpful but noone spoke English which might be an issue if your Spanish is weak.They have 2 computers with free Internet in the lobby which was good. I stayed in 2 rooms, one at the back on the lightwell which was a bit dark  old fashioned as another reviewer mentioned. I requested a move to a room overlooking the street. This room was much nicer, better lights  bathroom but there was a lot of noise from the street. If you have never been here you should know that Mexico City is a very noisy place. Car horns blasting, old VW beetle engines revving, traffic cops blowing their whistles. I founfd it difficult to get to sleep at night due to the noise  was always woken early by more noise. In retrospect I would rather have stayed in one of the back rooms.MSW 
