<Author>Seattle07
<Content>Cheap near Zocalo Very inexpensive. We paid only $25 per night.Rooms in the back are dark, on airwells, and unpleasant. But rooms in the front, facing the street are light, airy and very nice. The hotel is remodeling, so all rooms may improve in the future. Good location, two blocks from Zocalo. Good small restaurant on premises, free email in lobby. Said to be an unsafe area at night but didn't feel scary to this single woman. Staff very nice and helpful. 
